__de__ When I was a student here in Oxford in the 1970s , the future of the world was bleak .
__de__ The population explosion was unstoppable .
__de__ Global famine was inevitable .
__de__ A cancer epidemic caused by chemicals in the environment was going to shorten our lives .
__de__ The acid rain was falling on the forests .
__de__ The desert was advancing by a mile or two a year .
__de__ The oil was running out , and a nuclear winter would finish us off .
__de__ None of those things happened , ( Laughter ) and astonishingly , if you look at what actually happened in my lifetime , the average per-capita income of the average person on the planet , in real terms , adjusted for inflation , has tripled .
__de__ Lifespan is up by 30 percent in my lifetime .
__de__ Child mortality is down by two-thirds .
__de__ Per-capita food production is up by a third .
__de__ And all this at a time when the population has doubled .
__de__ How did we achieve that , whether you think it &apos;s a good thing or not ?
__de__ How did we achieve that ?
__de__ How did we become the only species that becomes more prosperous as it becomes more populous ?
